ods%20to%20manage%20with%20less%20water%2C%20NDTV%20visited%20some%20parched%20areas%20and%20spoke%20to%20them%20about%20how%20life%20has%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20of%20suburban%20Babusapalya%20are%20dependent%20on%20water%20tankers%20for%20their%20daily%20supply%2C%20and%20that%20has%20taken%20a%20severe%20hit%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20four%20tankers%20daily.%20We%20are%20getting%20only%20one%20or%20two.%20We%20are%20facing%20huge%20problems%20over%20the%20past%20two-three%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20resident%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20the%20city%20administration's%20order%20to%20fix%20tanker%20water%20rates%20has%20helped%2C%20a%20resident%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20rates%20have%20stabilised%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20remains%20huge.%20We%20are%20not%20getting%20tankers%20on%20time%20because%20of%20high%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20resident%20of%20an%20apartment%20complex%20in%20the%20area%20was%20leaving%20for%20work.%20When%20NDTV%20asked%20her%20about%20the%20towering%20water%20crisis%2C%20she%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20baby%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult.%20Tankers%20are%20not%20coming.%20The%20government%20has%20reduced%20the%20prices%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20coming.%20Even%20if%20they%20come%2C%20the%20water%20is%20not%20sufficient.%20I%20don't%20know%20when%20this%20will%20get%20resolved%20and%20when%20we%20will%20get%20back%20to%20normal%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20they%20are%20hopeful%20of%20better%20times%20once%20the%20monsoon%20comes%2C%20a%20resident%20flagged%20problems%20with%20the%20way%20in%20which%20successive%20governments%20implemented%20development%20projects.%20%26quot%3BThey%20did%20not%20consider%20the%20(overall)%20well-being%20of%20people.%20The%20focus%20has%20been%20on%20building%20apartments%20and%20roads%2C%20but%20we%20need%20to%20work%20on%20the%20groundwater%20level.%20It%20has%20never%20been%20done.%20I%20have%20been%20here%2015%20years.%20I%20have%20never%20seen%20such%20measures%20by%20any%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20people%20are%20waiting%20in%20kilometre-long%20queues%20for%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20resident%20said%20he%20took%20a%20bath%205%20times%20over%20the%20past%20one%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru%20primarily%20gets%20its%20water%20supply%20from%20two%20sources%20-%20Cauvery%20river%20and%20groundwater.%20For%20most%20non-drinking%20uses%2C%20recycled%20water%20processed%20by%20sewage%20treatment%20plants%20is%20used.%20With%20no%20rain%20for%20a%20while%20now%2C%20the%20primary%20sources%20have%20been%20stretched%20to%20their%20limits.%20Bengaluru%20needs%202%2C600-2%2C800%20million%20litres%20of%20water%20daily%2C%20and%20the%20current%20supply%20is%20half%20of%20what's%20required.%C2%A0The%20result%20is%20a%20daily%20struggle%20for%20the%20city's%20residents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20have%20responded%20with%20fixed%20rates%20for%20tankers%20supplying%20water%20to%20residential%20areas%20following%20allegations%20of%20extortion.%20Fines%20have%20been%20announced%20for%20use%20of%20drinking%20water%20for%20cleaning%20vehicles%2C%20gardening%20or%20construction%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20water%20crisis%20has%20hit%20hospitals%20too.%20Brookfield%20Hospital%20near%20Whitefield%2C%20one%20of%20the%20parched%20areas%20in%20the%20city%20right%20now%2C%20depends%20on%20water%20tankers%20and%20needs%2024%2C000%20litres%20in%20three%20days.%20That's%20not%20all%2C%205%2C000%20litres%20are%20needed%20daily%20just%20for%20the%20dialysis%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Pradeep%20Kumar%2C%20medical%20officer%20of%20Brookfield%20Hospital%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20recycling%20water%20and%20using%20it%20along%20with%20regular%20water%20for%20washing%20and%20cleaning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru%20has%20a%20huge%20chunk%20of%20the%20country's%20migrant%20techies%2C%20who%20have%20flocked%20to%20the%20IT%20hub%20for%20the%20opportunities%20it%20offers.%20Now%2C%20they%20are%20looking%20at%20work-from-home%20options%20to%20minimise%20water%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShruthi%2C%20an%20engineer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWork-from-home%20will%20be%20a%20viable%20option%2C%20but%20only%20if%20people%20actually%20went%20home%20so%20that%20the%20population%20is%20reduced%20and%20water%20consumption%20drops.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru%20may%20be%20parched%2C%20but%20the%20political%20pot%20is%20boiling.%20The%20Opposition%20BJP%20has%20warned%20of%20protests%2C%20with%20Bengaluru%20South%20MP%20Tejasvi%20Surya%20accusing%20the%20Congress%20government%20of%20negligence.%20%26quot%3BThe%20government%20failed%20to%20take%20up%20precautionary%20measures.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20this%20negligence%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Bengaluru%20are%20facing%20this%20tough%20water%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20has%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Chief%20Minister%20DK%20Shivakumar%20has%20brushed%20aside%20the%20allegations.%20%26quot%3BBJP%20must%20protest%20in%20Delhi%20for%20projects%20like%20Mahadayi.%20People%20like%20(former%20Chief%20Minister)%20Jagadish%20Shettar%20and%20(Union%20Minister)%20Prahlad%20Joshi%20will%20also%20benefit%20from%20drinking%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20media.%20The%20Mahadayi%20project%20plans%20to%20divert%20river%20water%20to%20parched%20areas%20of%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20is%20the%20situation%20that%20cricket%20authorities%20are%20discussing%20if%20the%20M%20Chinnaswamy%20cricket%20stadium%20can%20host%20IPL%20matches%20later%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20group%20of%20friends%20that%20has%20gathered%20at%20a%20coffee%20shop%20said%20the%20situation%20now%20is%20difficult%20to%20manage.%20Asked%20if%20the%20government's%20steps%20are%20going%20to%20help%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20one%20of%20them%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20only%20verbal%20diarrhoea.%20I%20don't%20think%20the%20government%20is%20going%20to%20provide%20a%20better%20lifestyle%20to%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20residents%20said%20they%20meet%20at%20the%20coffee%20shop%20daily%20after%20playing%20badminton.%C2%A0%26quot%3BWe%20stay%20in%20Pragati%20township.%20The%20government%20last%20year%20provided%20nine%20borewells%20for%20us.%20We%20used%20to%20get%20water%20till%20last%20month%2C%20but%20suddenly%20we%20came%20to%20know%20all%20the%20borewells%20have%20dried%20up.%20Getting%20water%20from%20tankers%20is%20very%20difficult%20because%20we%20have%20to%20book%20well%20in%20advance.%20We%20were%20paying%20Rs%20700-800%20(for%20water).%20Now%20the%20cost%20has%20gone%20up%20to%20Rs%201%2C500-Rs%202%2C000.%20And%20we%20are%20in%20March.%20So%20we%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20situation%20will%20be%20if%20it%20does%20not%20rain.%20The%20civic%20body%20has%20initiated%20online%20water%20supply%2C%20but%20that%20has%20not%20been%20activated%20yet.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20if%20they%20take%20over%20the%20tankers%2C%20will%20we%20get%20water%20on%20time%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20residents%20said%20the%20situation%20won't%20be%20resolved%20overnight.%20%26quot%3BDigging%20more%20borewells%20or%20giving%20tankers%20won't%20help.%20The%20government%20has%20to%20plan%20for%20at%20least%2020%20years.%20Only%20then%20will%20this%20problem%20be%20resolved%20permanently%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20resident%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20said%20not%20everything%20can%20be%20done%20by%20the%20government.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20important%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Bengaluru%20to%20conserve%20water.%20We%20have%20to%20find%20solutions%20too.%20We%20cannot%20put%20everything%20on%20the%20government.%20We%20should%20also%20take%20initiatives%20to%20save%20water.%20That%20will%20help%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710309960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A