e%20potentially%20lucrative%20satellite-launch%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20wants%20to%20assess%20if%20it%20can%20quickly%20launch%20temporary%2C%20small%20satellites%20when%20and%20if%20its%20existing%20spy%20satellites%20malfunction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKairos%20had%20been%20hoped%20to%20put%20the%20satellite%20into%20the%20orbit%20around%2051%20minutes%20after%20the%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpace%20One%20was%20established%20in%202018%20by%20a%20team%20of%20major%20Japanese%20tech%20businesses%2C%20including%20Canon%20Electronics%2C%20IHI%20Aerospace%2C%20construction%20firm%20Shimizu%20and%20the%20government-owned%20Development%20Bank%20of%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20July%20another%20Japanese%20rocket%20engine%20exploded%20during%20a%20test%20around%2050%20seconds%20after%20ignition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20solid-fuel%20Epsilon%20S%20was%20an%20improved%20version%20of%20the%20Epsilon%20rocket%20that%20had%20failed%20to%20launch%20the%20previous%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20testing%20site%20in%20the%20northern%20prefecture%20of%20Akita%20was%20engulfed%20in%20flames%20and%20a%20huge%20plume%20of%20grey%20smoke%20rose%20into%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20malfunction%20came%20after%20Tokyo%20in%20March%202023%20had%20seen%20its%20second%20attempt%20to%20launch%20its%20next-generation%20H3%20rocket%20fail%20after%20liftoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20though%20Japan's%20space%20agency%20toasted%20a%20successful%20blast-off%20for%20its%20new%20flagship%20rocket%2C%20the%20H3%2C%20after%20years%20of%20delays%20and%20two%20previous%20failed%20attempts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20H3%20launched%20from%20the%20Tanegashima%20Space%20Center%20in%20southwestern%20Japan%2C%20sparking%20cheers%20and%20applause%20at%20JAXA%20control%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20mooted%20as%20a%20rival%20to%20SpaceX's%20Falcon%209%2C%20and%20could%20one%20day%20deliver%20cargo%20to%20bases%20on%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5C