g%20heart%20rate%20can%20be%20a%20good%20sign%20of%20overall%20fitness%2C%20heart%20health%2C%20and%20longevity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20lower%20resting%20heart%20rate%20indicates%20your%20heart%20is%20stronger%20and%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20improve%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%20over%20time%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20high-intensity%20exercise%20and%20light%20cardio.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStop%20what%20you're%20doing%20%E2%80%94%20how's%20your%20heart%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20strong%2C%20healthy%20heart%20isn't%20just%20about%20keeping%20up%20during%20exercise.%20Measuring%20how%20well%20your%20heart%20works%20at%20rest%20is%20just%20as%20important%20for%20unlocking%20a%20longer%20life%20and%20better%20fitness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20resting%20heart%20rate%20(how%20many%20times%20your%20heart%20beats%20per%20minute%20while%20you're%20calm%20and%20sitting%20or%20lying%20down)%20can%20be%20a%20helpful%20sign%20of%20overall%20health%20and%20fitness%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Edo%20Paz%2C%20a%20cardiologist%20at%20White%20Plains%20Hospital%20and%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20medical%20affairs%20at%20the%20digital%20health%20company%20Hello%20Heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20resting%20heart%20rate%20tells%20you%20so%20much%20about%20your%20cardiovascular%20fitness%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Unlike%20other%20measures%20of%20heart%20health%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvo2-max-explained-what-is-good-how-improve-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVO2%20max%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20go%20into%20a%20lab%20to%20track%20it%20accurately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20tech%20millionaire%20or%20a%20biohacking%20enthusiast%2C%20you're%20keeping%20tabs%20on%20this%20stat.%20It's%20something%20the%20Bryan%20Johnsons%20of%20this%20world%20tout%20as%20proof%20that%20they're%20winning%20the%20race%20against%20aging.%20The%20rest%20of%20us%20are%20getting%20increasingly%20acquainted%20with%20our%20resting%20heart%20rates%2C%20too%2C%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20smartwatches%20and%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Ffitness-wearables-trackers-pros-cons-wellness-experts-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efitness%20wearables%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20measure%20your%20cardiovascular%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20bad%20thing.%20Knowing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fwhat-is-a-good-resting-heart-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyour%20resting%20heart%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20how%20it%20changes%20over%20time%20can%20help%20you%20keep%20tabs%20on%20your%20overall%20health%20and%20make%20the%20most%20of%20your%20workouts%20for%20a%20longer%2C%20healthier%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20should%20you%20care%20about%20resting%20heart%20rate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20resting%20heart%20rate%2C%20a%20lower%20number%20is%20better%20for%20health%20and%20fitness%2C%20said%20Mike%20Thomson%2C%20personal%20trainer%20and%20run%20coach%20at%20Life%20Time%20Overland%20Park%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20have%20a%20low%20resting%20heart%20rate%2C%20indicating%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20cardiovascular%20fitness.%20This%20indicates%20that%20the%20heart%20doesn't%20have%20to%20do%20as%20much%20work%20to%20maintain%20bodily%20function.%20A%20heart%20that%20must%20beat%20more%20could%20be%20stressed%2C%20under-rested%2C%20inflamed%2C%20or%20have%20limited%20cardiovascular%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnywhere%20from%2060%20to%20100%20beats%20per%20minute%20is%20typically%20considered%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-good-resting-heart-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enormal%20resting%20heart%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Paz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthletes%2C%20especially%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-tips-older-athlete-exercise-diet-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eendurance%20sports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20can%20have%20a%20resting%20heart%20rate%20as%20low%20as%2040%20beats%20per%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20don't%20worry%20too%20much%20about%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%20at%20any%20one%20point%20in%20time%2C%20said%20Kate%20Baird%2C%20exercise%20physiologist%20at%20the%20Hospital%20for%20Special%20Surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20influenced%20by%20daily%20factors%20like%20how%20well%20you%20slept%2C%20whether%20you're%20stressed%2C%20and%20if%20you're%20hydrated%20or%20not%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%20important%20than%20a%20single%20measure%20of%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%20is%20how%20it%20changes%20over%20time%2C%20Baird%20said.%20If%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%20is%20trending%20up%20over%20time%2C%20that's%20a%20good%20indicator%20that%20you're%20becoming%20more%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20track%20relative%20changes%20to%20see%20that%20the%20system%20is%20getting%20stronger%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20can%20you%20improve%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20heart%20is%20a%20muscle.%20As%20with%20your%20biceps%20or%20your%20quads%2C%20you%20can%20exercise%20to%20make%20it%20stronger%20and%20more%20effective.%20As%20you%20strengthen%20your%20heart%2C%20it%20can%20operate%20more%20efficiently%2C%20which%20means%20it%20doesn't%20need%20to%20work%20as%20hard%20to%20keep%20you%20functioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20you%20train%2C%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%20is%20going%20to%20go%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Paz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20high-intensity%20and%20low-intensity%20workouts%20benefit%20your%20heart%2C%20so%20a%20mix%20of%20both%20is%20a%20good%20bet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomson%20said%20he%20treats%20exercise%20like%20investing%20in%20better%20heart%20health%20by%20diversifying%20his%20fitness%20portfolio%2C%20spending%20about%2080%25%20of%20the%20time%20exercising%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-zone-2-cardio-exercise-training-benefits-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20at%20a%20steady%2C%20easy%20pace%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20remaining%2020%25%20doing%20high-intensity%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20keep%20things%20simple%2C%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20easy%20effort%20cardio%20where%20you%20can%20have%20a%20conversation%20while%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20also%20recommend%20training%201-2%20times%20a%20week%20with%20high%20intensity%20where%20you%20get%20extremely%20out%20of%20breath.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20high%20intensity%2C%20Thomson%20recommends%20trying%20workouts%20such%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20rounds%20of%20five%20minutes%20of%20hard%20cardio%2C%20with%20three%20minutes%20of%20rest%20between%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESprinting%20or%20running%20uphill%20for%2030%20seconds%2C%20resting%20for%2090%20seconds%2C%20and%20repeating%20for%2010-15%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20while%20sprinting%20is%20great%20for%20high-intensity%2C%20too%20much%20can%20leave%20you%20prone%20to%20injury%2C%20so%20mix%20it%20up%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcardio-exercises-better-than-running-to-build-muscle-stamina-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20heart-pumping%20exercises%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20a%20sled%20push%20or%20pull%2C%20ski%20erg%20machine%2C%20assault%20bike%2C%20or%20rower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20your%20fitness%20level%2C%20examples%20of%20low-intensity%20workouts%20include%20activities%20like%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E45%20minutes%20to%20an%20hour%20of%20brisk%20walking%20or%20light%20jogging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E45%20minutes%20of%20biking%20at%20a%20st